This paper is about weakly supervised semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a fully end-to-end network, which involves training a model to predict segmentation maps, indicating that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of image-level labels and classification, which suggests that natural language processing (cs.CL) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of performance metrics, indicating that multimedia (cs.MM) may also be a relevant sub-category.
